        "content": "<p>It seems like <a href=\"https://rust-lang.github.io/rfcs/1946-intra-rustdoc-links.html#linking-to-fields\">https://rust-lang.github.io/rfcs/1946-intra-rustdoc-links.html#linking-to-fields</a> never got to be implemented, right?</p>\n<p>What is a proper way of making a link to a field?</p>\n<p>Also, using the syntax described in the RFC seems to be broken, for example:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#![warn(rustdoc::broken_intra_doc_links)]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">Struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">field</span>: <span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"sd\">/// [`field`](Struct.field)</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">f</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The link links to <code>crate/Struct.field</code> which doesn't exist, no warning produced whatsoever.</p>",
        "id": 276632519,
        "sender_full_name": "Waffle Lapkin",
        "timestamp": 1648220886
